{{ define "keys-mint-modal" }}
<aside class="lc-drawer"
       role="dialog"
       aria-modal="true"
       aria-labelledby="lc-mint-title"
       x-data="{ open: true, copied: false, plaintext: {{ .JustMinted.RawKey | printf "%q" }} }"
       x-trap.inert.noscroll="open"
       x-on:keydown.escape.window="open = false; plaintext = ''"
       x-show="open">
  <div class="lc-drawer-backdrop" x-on:click="open = false; plaintext = ''"></div>
  <div class="lc-drawer-panel">
    <header class="lc-drawer-header">
      <h2 id="lc-mint-title" class="lc-drawer-title">New API key &mdash; copy now, it will not appear again</h2>
      {{- /* Slice 5 fix-up r1 UX-L1: close button moved from
         lc-link-button (~16x16 click target) to lc-secondary-button
         + × glyph (~28x28 click target) to meet the 24x24 minimum
         touch-target. The dialog also has an "I copied it, close"
         CTA as the primary affordance; this corner button is the
         secondary escape hatch. */ -}}
      <button type="button" class="lc-secondary-button" aria-label="Close" x-on:click="open = false; plaintext = ''">&times;</button>
    </header>
    <div class="lc-drawer-body">
      <p class="lc-text-muted">Key ID: <code class="lc-mono">{{ .JustMinted.KeyID }}</code> &mdash; prefix <code class="lc-mono">{{ .JustMinted.KeyPrefix }}</code></p>
      {{- /* Slice 5 fix-up r1 BH-L3: copy softened from "removes the
         value from the page" to "removes the value from the visible
         UI" — the plaintext literal still sits inside the
         x-data="plaintext: …" attribute on the parent aside element
         until the next page load, so promising "from the page" is
         technically incorrect. Closing the modal does remove it from
         the visible DOM tree (x-show goes false) and the page
         carries Cache-Control: no-store + Referrer-Policy:
         no-referrer headers so back-button history + outbound
         referrers don't surface it. A future iteration could load
         the plaintext via x-init then immediately removeAttribute(
         "x-data") to scrub the source attribute too; deferred. */ -}}
      <div class="lc-banner lc-banner--warn" role="status">
        Treat the plaintext key below as bearer-equivalent. The gateway never stores it in recoverable form &mdash; this is the only chance to copy it. Closing this dialog removes the value from the visible UI.
      </div>
      <label class="lc-text-muted" for="lc-mint-raw">Plaintext key</label>
      <pre class="lc-codeblock"><code id="lc-mint-raw" x-text="plaintext"></code></pre>
      <div class="lc-card-actions">
        <button type="button"
                class="lc-primary-button"
                x-on:click="navigator.clipboard.writeText(plaintext).then(() => { copied = true; setTimeout(() => copied = false, 5000); })">Copy key</button>
        <span class="lc-pill lc-pill--ok" x-show="copied" x-transition>Copied</span>
        <button type="button"
                class="lc-secondary-button"
                x-on:click="open = false; plaintext = ''">I copied it, close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</aside>
{{ end }}
